Definition.WordDefinition:
lumberjack \lum"ber*jack`\ n. 1. a person who works at lumbering; a lumberman.
Syn: lumberman, timberman. [WordNet 1.5]
2. (Zool.) The grey jay. [Canadian] [PJC]
lumberjack n 1: a person who fells trees [syn: {lumberman}, {feller}, {faller}] 2: a short warm outer jacket [syn: {lumber jacket}]
